---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import trainingBanner1 from '../assets/images/training-banner1.JPG';
import trainingBanner2 from '../assets/images/training-banner2.JPG';
import trainingBanner3 from '../assets/images/training-banner3.JPG';
---

<Layout>
  <Navigation />
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 w-full">
      <div>
        <Image src={trainingBanner1} alt="Flight training in action" class="w-full h-full object-cover shadow-md" />
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col h-full">
        <Image src={trainingBanner2} alt="Student and instructor preflight" class="w-full aspect-3/1 object-cover shadow-md" />
        <Image src={trainingBanner3} alt="Aircraft on the ramp" class="w-full aspect-3/1 object-cover shadow-md" />
      </div>
    </div>
  <section class="bg-zinc-950 pb-20 px-8 py-20 min-h-screen">
    
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-5xl">
      
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-12 text-center">training</h1>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-12 text-left">pilot license</h2>
      <div class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-zinc-200 text-lg leading-relaxed text-justify mb-6">
          There are plenty of resources online outlining the process of getting different licenses, so we take a slightly different approach. Below, we walk you through the licenses in a natural progression, outlining the privileges of each. To help you decide on your piloting pathway, we base our advice on a flow chart of yes/no questions. If you have more questions, email <a href="mailto:mcgillflyingclub@gmail.com?subject=[FT]" class="text-blue-400 underline">mcgillflyingclub@gmail.com</a> with the [FT] tag in your title. Ready to begin? Visit our <a href="#partner" class="text-blue-400 underline">Partner Flight School</a> section or their website for more details.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Ground School (GS) Division</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-200 text-lg leading-relaxed text-justify mb-4">
          The GS Division organizes and runs ground school courses, including Private Pilot's License (PPL) ground school since 2012, and now offers courses for other license types. In 2015, ground school was opened to the public. Today, we partner with Harv's Air to provide discounted training to all pilots.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">The Ground School</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-200 text-lg leading-relaxed text-justify mb-4">
          Ground school is the theoretical/classroom component of your flight training. You must complete both ground school and practical flying to earn your licenseâ€”much like a written and road test for a driver's license. Your first ground school will likely be for the PPL, including prep for the Student Pilot Permit, PSTAR, and PPAER. Once you complete the materials, you'll get a recommendation for the written exams. For exam site info, contact our FT Division.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Ground School at McGill</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-200 text-lg leading-relaxed text-justify mb-4">
          Our partnership with Harv's Air makes ground school affordable and flexible. Harv's Air's industry-leading virtual ground school prepares you for Transport Canada exams. Many of our execs have succeeded through this program. For more info, use the sidebar or CONTACT tab.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Available Courses</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-200 mb-4">
          <li>Recreational Pilot Permit (RPP)</li>
          <li>Private Pilot License (PPL)</li>
          <li>Commercial Pilot License (CPL)</li>
          <li>Instrument and Multi-engine Rating (INRAT)</li>
          <li>Instructor's Rating (AIRAF/AIRAT)</li>
          <li>Conversion courses (FAA &rarr; Transport Canada) on request</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-zinc-200 text-lg leading-relaxed text-justify mb-4">
          Foreign license conversion courses are not available directly; contact us with [FT] in your email title for more info.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Course Duration and Schedule</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-200 mb-4">
          <li>Self-paced, 270-day access across devices</li>
          <li>Includes written exam prep and pre-lesson air exercise videos</li>
          <li>Certificate and instructor letter of recommendation upon completion</li>
          <li>Progress is saved; renew access at a lower price if needed</li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Cost</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-200 text-lg leading-relaxed text-justify mb-4">
          Cost varies by license type. See Harv's Air's website for current prices.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Ground School Contacts</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-200 mb-4">
          <li>Email us via the CONTACT tab with [GS] for ground school info</li>
          <li>Email with [FT] for info on integrating ground school into your training</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Ground School Partner</h4>
          <a href="https://www.harvsair.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-400 underline">Visit Harv's Air</a>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Ground School Code Request</h4>
          <p class="text-zinc-200">To receive a discount code, email us with [FT] at the start of your email title.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Useful Links</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-200">
            <li><a href="https://www.tc.gc.ca/en/services/aviation/licensing-examinations.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-400 underline">Transport Canada Licensing & Exams</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.tc.gc.ca/en/services/aviation/private-pilot-licence.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-400 underline">Private Pilot License Guide</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.tc.gc.ca/en/services/aviation/instrument-rating.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-400 underline">Instrument Rating Guide</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.tc.gc.ca/en/services/aviation/commercial-pilot-licence.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-400 underline">Commercial Pilot License Guide</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.tc.gc.ca/en/services/aviation/instructor-rating.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-400 underline">Instructor's Rating Guide</a></li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-zinc-200 mt-2">Multi-Engine Rating does not require a written exam.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="partner" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Partner Flight School (FTU Division)</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-200 text-lg leading-relaxed text-justify mb-4">
          We are proud partners with <strong>ALM Par Avion</strong> based at Montreal/Beloeil (CSB3). Our partnership makes starting or continuing flight training easier and ensures up-to-date, accurate information. In case of conflicting info, ALM Par Avion's website takes precedence.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">School and Airport Overview</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-200 text-lg leading-relaxed text-justify mb-4">
          ALM Par Avion is a local Montreal flight training unit at Beloeil Airport. The school has a club-like atmosphere, with instructors teaching every license and rating issued by Transport Canada. They also offer aerial work and aircraft charters.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Instruction Offered</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-200 mb-4">
          <li>Private Pilot's License</li>
          <li>Commercial Pilot's License</li>
          <li>Night Rating</li>
          <li>Instrument Rating (Class 1 or 3)</li>
          <li>Instructor's Rating (French only)</li>
          <li>Multi-Engine Rating</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://almparavion.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-400 underline">Visit ALM Par Avion</a>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-zinc-900 rounded-lg p-6 mt-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Contact</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-200 mb-2">Email: <a href="mailto:mcgillflyingclub@gmail.com" class="text-blue-400 underline">mcgillflyingclub@gmail.com</a></p>
        <p class="text-zinc-200">(Use [GS] or [FT] tag in your email title)</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
